"Flores L.A., Martínez L.I., Ferrer C.M., Gallego V.P., Bermejo A.S.","A spatial high-resolution model of the dynamics of agricultural land use",2008,"Agricultural Economics","38","2",,"233","245",,,10.1111/j.1574-0862.2007.00296.x,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-41749099678&partnerID=40&md5=a66d0dc189abff141c9f1adb1d9ab4a2","Departamento de Economía Y Ciencias Sociales Agrarias, Escuela Técnica Superior de Ingenieros Agrónomos, Universidad Politécnica de Madrid, Avda Complutense sn, 28040, Madrid, Spain; Departamento de Explotación de Recursos Minerales Y Obras Subterráneas, Universidad Politécnica de Madrid, Spain; Departamento Interdisciplinar de Desarrollo Sostenible, Universidad Católica de Ávila, Spain","Flores, L.A., Departamento de Economía Y Ciencias Sociales Agrarias, Escuela Técnica Superior de Ingenieros Agrónomos, Universidad Politécnica de Madrid, Avda Complutense sn, 28040, Madrid, Spain; Martínez, L.I., Departamento de Explotación de Recursos Minerales Y Obras Subterráneas, Universidad Politécnica de Madrid, Spain; Ferrer, C.M., Departamento de Economía Y Ciencias Sociales Agrarias, Escuela Técnica Superior de Ingenieros Agrónomos, Universidad Politécnica de Madrid, Avda Complutense sn, 28040, Madrid, Spain; Gallego, V.P., Departamento de Economía Y Ciencias Sociales Agrarias, Escuela Técnica Superior de Ingenieros Agrónomos, Universidad Politécnica de Madrid, Avda Complutense sn, 28040, Madrid, Spain, Departamento Interdisciplinar de Desarrollo Sostenible, Universidad Católica de Ávila, Spain; Bermejo, A.S., Departamento de Economía Y Ciencias Sociales Agrarias, Escuela Técnica Superior de Ingenieros Agrónomos, Universidad Politécnica de Madrid, Avda Complutense sn, 28040, Madrid, Spain","An area model is presented for agricultural land use, based on a generalized linear mixed model. This model is spatially explicit and dynamic and, although it uses aggregated data, allows for heterogeneity of behavior among individual farmers. The parameters of the fixed component of the model are obtained using an estimation equations approach, and the structure of spatiotemporal correlation is assessed using empirical semivariograms. The model is illustrated using as an example the dynamics of agricultural land use in the Lower Guadalquivir area in Spain. A simulation study indicates that the model gives poor results if the heterogeneity of individual behavior and spatiotemporal autocorrelation are ignored. © 2008 International Association of Agricultural Economists.","Aggregation ecological fallacy; Generalized linear mixed models; Semivariogram models for spatiotemporal autocorrelation structures; Spatial and dynamic choice models","agricultural modeling; arable land; autocorrelation; data interpretation; empirical analysis; farmers attitude; land use; spatiotemporal analysis; variogram; Andalucia; Eurasia; Europe; Guadalquivir Basin; Southern Europe; Spain",,,,,,"Adams, R.M., Rosenzweig, C., Peart, R.M., Ritchie, J.T., McCarl, B.A., Glyer, J.D., Curry, R.B., Allen Jr., L.H., Global climate change and U.S. agriculture (1990) Nature, 345, pp. 219-224; Adams, R.M., McCarl, B.A., Dudek, D.J., Glyer, J.D., A reassessment of the economic effects of global climate change on U.S. agriculture (1995) Clim. Change, 30, pp. 147-167; Albert, P.S., McShane, L.M., A generalized estimating equations approach for spatially correlated binary data: Applications to the analysis of neuroimaging data (1995) Biometrics, 51, pp. 627-638; Alig, R.J., Econometric analysis of the factors influencing forest acreage trends in the South-east (1986) For. Sci., 32, pp. 119-134; Ambrosio, L., Iglesias, L., Marín, C., Systematic simple design for the estimation of spatial means (2003) Environmetrics, 14, pp. 45-61; Baker, S.G., The multinomial-Poisson transformation (1994) Statistician, 43, pp. 495-504; Baltzer, H., Braun, P.W., Köhler, W., Cellular automata models for vegetation dynamics (1998) Ecol. Models, 107, pp. 113-125; Boote, 